1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 20.1-03-04 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to when licenses to hunt, fish, or trap are not required of landowners.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 20.1-03-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 20.1-03-04. When licenses to hunt, fish, or trap not required of residents.
7 Subject to the provisions of this title:
8 1. Any landowner or resident, or any member of the resident's family residing customarily
9 with the resident, may hunt small game, fish, or trap during the open season without a
10 license upon land owned or leased by the landowner or resident.
11 2. Residents or nonresidents under the age of sixteen years may fish without a fishing
12 license.
13 3. Residents may fish at a private fish hatchery without a resident fishing license.
14 4. Life skills and transition center patients, North Dakota youth correctional center
15 students, school for the deaf students, North Dakota vision services - school for the
16 blind students, state hospital patients, clients of regional human service centers under
17 direct therapeutic care, and residents of facilities licensed by the department of health
18 and human services may fish without a resident fishing license. Patients of these
19 institutions must be identified. The department shall issue authority to each institution.
20 5. Residents may fish without a resident fishing license on free fishing days. The date of
21 these free fishing days may be set by proclamation by the governor.
22 6. Residents under age sixteen may take fur-bearers without a fur-bearer license.
23 7. Residents under age sixteen may take small game or waterfowl without a small game
24 license.
