1 8. Residents who are enrolled as students or serving as certified instructors during
2 official aquatics education program events of the game and fish department may be
3 granted free fishing privileges by discretion of the director.
4 9. Upon presentation of valid leave papers and a valid North Dakota operator's license, a
5 resident who is on leave and is on active duty as a member of the United States
6 armed forces or the United States merchant marine may hunt small game, fish, or trap
7 during the open season without a license.
